Aileen Tan ( simplified Chinese : 陈丽贞 ; pinyin : Chén Lìzhēn ; born 18 October 1966 ) is a versatile actress in Singapore . Because of her age , Singaporeans seldom see her on television nowadays . Her friends include award - winning actress Huang Biren and Pan Lingling . In September 2006 , Aileen went for an abortion after being pregnant for a week due to ectopic pregnancy . Aileen is best known for her good acting skills and is a multi - nominee in the Best Actress category in the annual Star Awards . She was nominated for Best Actress in Years 1994 , 1995 , 1996 , 1997 , 2001 , 2002 and 2003 . In 2006 , she appeared in two high - profile Singapore dramas , Women of Times and Measure of Man , the latter drama having the 2nd highest viewership drama rate for year 2006 . However , Aileen was not nominated for either role at the Star Awards 2006 . Audience would get to see her in her next upcoming drama serial , Mars vs Venus , on 1 May 2007 . On 10 March 2007 , Aileen was voted as the most popular actress aged 40 and above by TV audience . She beat down hot favoutites such as Zoe Tay and Xiang Yun . 